OPTIONS(description="This BigQuery table stores FHIR data related to healthcare encounters, which are interactions between a patient and healthcare provider(s) for the purpose of providing healthcare services or assessing the health status of a patient. Each record in the table represents a single encounter and includes key attributes such as encounter ID, patient reference, encounter status, class, type, priority, subject, participant details, appointment reference, period of the encounter, length, reason code, diagnosis, account reference, hospitalization details, location, service provider, and part of another encounter if applicable. The table is designed to support interoperability and data exchange in healthcare settings, enabling efficient querying and analysis of encounter data for clinical, operational, and research purposes. The schema adheres to the FHIR standard, ensuring compatibility with other FHIR-compliant systems and facilitating integration into broader healthcare data ecosystems.");